            .col-xs-12.col-md-6
                h5.caps Design
                p At RevUnit, the heart of the design process, like everything we do, is focused on the end User Experience (UX). UX is the number one guiding force in all design.
                p Studies show 70% of projects fail due to lack of user acceptance. Source?
                p UX Design increases the success of Key Performance Indicators by 83%
                p In the creative process of any digital product, UX Designers use the designs and feedback generated during Rapid Prototyping and User Testing phases to create the rest of the experience. Designers focus on making the app intuitive and incorporating all functionality requirements while keeping the product visually attractive. 
                p Our design process uses tools to make collaboration easier between Designers and Developers when building the code. Each of our UX Designers is also talented in creating the User Interface--the actual graphics, buttons, colors, and icons users will see in the app. The creative process brings all of the problem solving to life in a real, visual way.
            .col-xs-12.col-md-6.kill-on-desktop
                .img-wrap
                    img(src="img/icon--build-2.svg")
        .row.process-row
            .col-xs-12.col-md-6
                h5.caps Development
                p While the creative team is in the early stages of designing, the development team goes to work. Developers use the user stories written in the early stages of Pre-flight to understand the level of complexity and purpose of each micro-experience. They use these stories to create the code needed to build the app. 
                p The development team works in short periods of time, known as sprints, which are essential to using the agile method. Sprints are defined as a set period of time, commonly two weeks. When planning a development process, development times are created based on the understanding of how many user stories the team can code in each sprint. 
                p Working with sprints allows for exceptional agility. If a new design is created or a current user story is reprioritized, sprints make it easy to predict how that adjustment will affect the overall product timeline. With user stories and sprints, the development process becomes fluid and transparent for the entire team as they build the MVP and prepare for launch.
            .col-xs-12.col-md-6
